                            Just read this article, and have to say that Mr. Mathe, you‚Äôre right on point.
And even though we‚Äôre commenting a few years later, these truths are still the same for 2016.
We found Kickstarter to be a little clunky with editing functions, but miles ahead of anything that IGG offered. The mere fact that on KS you‚Äôll garner a lot of support by discovery alone gives KS a tremendous edge.
For our Kickstarter, about 50% of the funds came from people who just searched KS for new games and sports-related games. This helped greatly as our game is a niche market within a niche market ‚Äì so we definitely needed that boost from the KS platform.
Good job, James, and great article. I wish we‚Äôd have read this a while back ‚Äì would have been a little less tooth-pulling!
